<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCNALL NOT GETTING A LOT OF SYMPATHY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Poor Bruce McNall. The Walt Disney of his time, Bruce sought only to make the 
world a happier place.Now, admitted felon that he is, Bruce is maligned by 
Helene Elliott, and, worse yet, Tom Pollack, McNall's attorney, had his 
feelings hurt! 
</P>
<P>
 In response to Mr. Pollack's righteous indignation, I am left with the 
following question: If Mr. Pollack feels so strongly about the injustice of his 
client's public vilification, why doesn't he represent Bruce on a pro bono 
basis? 
</P>
<P>
 BRIAN PATRICK CLARKE 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 
