<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Consumers Keep on Spending: Despite smaller incomes in November, consumers 
kept up the furious spending pace that has fueled economic growth this year.At 
the same time, orders for big-ticket durable goods posted the biggest jump in 
three months. The Commerce Department said that consumer spending rose 0.6% in 
November, the seventh straight advance, including a 0.7% gain in October. 
Analysts also said the 3.4% jump in factory orders for durable goods was 
exaggerated by an unsustainable surge of aircraft and automobile bookings in 
November. 
