<P>
 Koll Real Estate Group Ordered to Pay IRS: The Internal Revenue Service 
ordered the home builder to pay $20.8 million to settle a tax dispute. Newport 
Beach-based Koll was sued earlier this year by Abex Inc. and Wheelabrator 
Technologies Inc. All three companies are former subsidiaries of Henley Group 
Inc. The tax dispute is related to Henley Group's sale in 1988 of a stake in 
the Santa Fe Southern Pacific railway. Koll said it intends to appeal. 
