<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPPORT FOR 'POPS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 News that "Evening at Pops" may die for lack of sponsor support leads me to 
suggest a change in PBS' approach to listener support: Allow program-specific 
contributions (" 'Pops' Could Go Pop," Morning Report, Nov. 21).I'd be glad to 
pay to support the Pops but would hate to have my dollars supporting the 
appalling new PBS quiz show and the crass infomercial series for outdoor gear. 
</P>
<P>
 I recognize that PBS needs the flexibility of undesignated contributions. How 
about a compromise: Permit 50% of each contribution to be earmarked for a 
favorite series while the other half goes into the general fund? 
</P>
<P>
 MICHAEL D. REAGAN 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 
</P>
