<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LAW TEST FOR PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In his Dec. 17 letter, Tibor Zelig criticized Esa-Pekka Salonen and Ernest 
Fleischmann of the Los Angeles Philharmonic for making anti-Proposition 187 
remarks while in Mexico ("Proving Music Knows No Borders," Nov. 24). 
</P>
<P>
 Zelig says the statements "demean the majority of California voters, including 
Philharmonic supporters." I wish someone would tell Zelig that just because a 
proposition is passed, it does not necessarily mean that it is constitutional. 
</P>
<P>
