<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: FORECAST: HAZY SKIES, HEAVY HOLIDAY TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County may be in for a wet and cloudy Christmas weekend, according to 
the National Weather Service bureau in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 There is a 70% chance of rain today, changing to showers later in the 
afternoon.There is also a 40% chance on showers on Christmas Day. And today, 
Sunday and Monday are all expected to be gloomy and overcast. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's definitely going to be cloudy," said Vladimir Ryshko of the National 
Weather Service, "and it will probably be rainy." 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, traffic is expected to be hectic throughout the holiday weekend, 
according to the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP began a maximum enforcement period last night that will put 70% of its 
personnel on roads, looking for unsafe vehicles, road hazards and drunk drivers 
for the remainder of the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 "We do expect a lot of traffic all weekend, since a lot of travelers either 
leave or go home," CHP Officer Staci Morse said. "There are a lot of things 
going on all weekend." MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
