COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN ARRESTED AFTER HIS TRUCK HITS BUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man was arrested on suspicion of drunk driving Friday after slamming 
his full-size pickup truck into the back of a Ventura commuter bus, slightly 
injuring a passenger and himself. 
</P>
<P>
 William Clayton Hartman III, 36, was arrested after police administered a 
blood test in connection with the 6:10 p.m. accident on Telephone Road east of 
Kimball Road, police said.He was taken to Ventura County Medical Center for 
treatment of minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger, Candice Valenzuela, 15, was treated at the scene for a bruised 
forehead. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Hartman was driving east on Telephone Road behind the bus and 
failed to stop when the bus slowed for a passenger stop, Cpl. Bryan Roberts 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I heard the brakes lock up," said Eric Prater, who lived near the accident. 
"It sounded like he hit a brick wall." 
</P>
<P>
 Roberts said he was unsure how fast the truck was traveling but said the 
vehicle was damaged beyond repair. The rear of the bus was smashed in the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Eastbound Telephone Road was closed for about two hours between Sterling 
Avenue and Kimball Road, police said. PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
