<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLINTON JOINS MALL CROWD FOR GIFT SHOPPING SPREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Clinton joined the ranks of last-minute Christmas shoppers Friday 
with a two-hour buying spree that included clothing and jewelry purchases made 
with a credit card. 
</P>
<P>
 Accompanied by two young aides and a small army of Secret Service bodyguards, 
Clinton plunged into a lunchtime shopping crowd at a mall in Washington's 
fashionable Georgetown neighborhood and headed straight to a music store. 
</P>
<P>
 Using a credit card, he purchased some videos there. Then it was on to a 
historic memorabilia store, men's and women's clothing stores, a jewelry store, 
a toy store, a toiletries store and finally a curio shop. 
</P>
<P>
 While Clinton kept his gift list to himself, it looked as if his wife, 
Hillary, and daughter, Chelsea, will find some nice presents under the 
Christmas tree Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 One of his purchases was a woven woman's vest that he found in a store 
specializing in accessories with a Latin American flavor. Reporters trailing 
after him also saw him buy a book and some jewelry. 
</P>
<P>
 During Clinton's whirlwind gift-buying excursion, fellow shoppers cheered and 
shouted: "Merry Christmas, Bill!" and got presidential smiles and waves in 
return. 
</P>
<P>
 While the President was shopping in Georgetown, Hillary Rodham Clinton and 
Chelsea were hunting for gifts across the Potomac River in Alexandria, Va. 
</P>
<P>
 A White House spokeswoman said they spent three hours canvassing stores in 
Alexandria's historic Old Town district, and completed their Christmas 
shopping. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clintons plan to spend Christmas at the White House with family members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
