COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SADDLEBACK TO OFFER CLASSES TO COMMUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The spring issue of Saddleback College community education department's class 
schedule is due to arrive in the mail the first week of January. 
</P>
<P>
 The college's community education department offers more than 200 non-credit 
courses, from painting to piano. There are also courses such as business 
writing, middle-management supervision, traffic school and Department of Motor 
Vehicle-approved motorcycle rider safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Students may register for classes by telephone, using MasterCard or Visa, 
mail, fax machine, and in person at the school's Administration and Governance 
Building, 28000 Marguerite Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration forms and instructions are on the back page of the course 
schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 582-4646.JEFF BEAN 
