<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; KIWANIS TREATS FOR ORANGEWOOD CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Acting on its motto of "children first," the Fountain Valley Kiwanis Club 
brightened the holiday season this week for 27 youngsters from the Orangewood 
Children's Home. 
</P>
<P>
 The 24-member community service group treated the children, ages 4 to 6, to 
lunch and a visit with Santa Claus.Each child also received a gift: a Barbie 
doll or Power Ranger figure. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really a special day for them," said Chris Fowler, Kiwanis president. 
Fowler added that the event also proved rewarding for club members -- 
especially when they saw the shine in the children's eyes as they clutched 
their gifts.  
</P>
<P>
 The Orange facility is for children who are in protective custody. Fowler said 
club members wanted to spread Christmas cheer to the children because they 
"aren't going to have a special Christmas. They're away from their families. 
For us, we felt that for a few hours at least, we can make it more special." 
</P>
<P>
 Fowler said the outpouring of gifts was so great that there were 60 extra 
toys, which will be donated to the Fairview Developmental Center in Costa Mesa. 
DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
