198 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The corner of Talbert Avenue and Bushard Street looks like any other suburban 
intersection today, with its sprinkling of strip malls and concrete walls that 
separate the busy roads from quiet neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
 But the crossroads is considered the birthplace of Fountain Valley.The area 
was once home to a general store, a church and other buildings. For the first 
half of the century, it served as a central trading post for farmers who lived 
in the area. For decades, the area was known as Talbert Village -- named after 
early developer James Talbert. 
</P>
<P>
 After World War II, the crossroads was slowly transformed. Today, only the 
church and a boarded-up building stand as reminders of Talbert Village. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Talk about an Orange County holiday tradition. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Glory of Christmas" Nativity program will be performed at 4:30, 6:30 and 
8:30 p.m. today at the Crystal Cathedral in Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 This 14th annual re-creation of Christ's birth features flying angels, singers 
and dancers. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticket prices range from $12 to $30. Performances will continue through 
Friday, Dec. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crystal Cathedral is at 12141 Lewis St. Reservations are available by 
calling (714) 54-GLORY. 
</P>
</TEXT>
