COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CYPRESS; FLEEING MEN HELD IN ARMED ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two 21-year-old men were arrested on suspicion of armed robbery early Friday 
after they were seen fleeing from the crime scene, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A Cypress police officer on duty saw Jerry Karl Sims and Anthony Eugene 
Cooley, both 21, running into an apartment complex at the same time he heard a 
radio report that a convenience store in the 5000 block of Lincoln Avenue had 
been robbed, according to police Sgt. Larry Jordan.The apartment complex was 
about a quarter of a block north of the convenience store, Jordan said. 
</P>
<P>
 La Palma and Cypress police surrounded the apartment complex and arrested both 
men about 2:30 a.m. with the assistance of police dogs, Peterson said. Nobody 
was injured during the arrest, and police say the stolen money was recovered. 
THAO HUA 
</P>
