<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: BUENA PARK; SHE WANTED A TOY CAR AND GETS A JOY RIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By NANCY HSU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The simple Christmas wish of a 4-year-old girl with leukemia -- a toy Barbie 
car -- is about to be granted in an unexpected way. 
</P>
<P>
 Mireya Garcia is this year's winner of a $1,000 shopping spree at Toys R Us, 
thanks to the Make-A-Wish Foundation of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6:15 a.m. today, Mireya will be surprised by a limousine at her front door 
that will take her to the Huntington Beach toy store. "Her original wish was 
for a Barbie car, so one of the other wish coordinators and myself decided we 
were going to embellish the wish," said Lyn Shermet, the foundation's wish 
granter. 
</P>
<P>
 Mireya was discharged Thursday from Children's Hospital of Orange County where 
she was undergoing chemotherapy, Shermet said. NANCY HSU 
</P>
</TEXT>
