<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; MUSEUM TO OFFER CHILDREN'S WORKSHOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Science and history will be explored in a series of workshops for children 
offered next week at the Discovery Museum of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 These hands-on workshops will be held from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "American Indian Adventures," scheduled for Tuesday, will be led by Mark 
Mendez of the Chumash Nation of Southern California.Mendez will teach children 
ages 6 through 12 about Native American folklore using crafts, games and 
storytelling. 
</P>
<P>
 "Insect Detectives," for ages 4 to 7, will be offered Wednesday. Children will 
make insect nets, go on a bug hunt, play games and make crafts. 
</P>
<P>
 "Eco-Art: Treasures From Trash" will be held Thursday for ages 6 to 12. 
Participants will play games and transform recyclable materials into bird 
feeders and other craft projects. 
</P>
<P>
 Fees are $5 for Discovery Museum members and $7 for non-members. 
</P>
<P>
 To register, call (714) 540-0404.ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
