<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL-AREA CROSS-COUNTRY TEAM; TOP BOYS' RUNNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eleazar Hernandez 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Camarillo 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Hernandez placed fifth in the Foot Locker national 
championships Dec. 10 after finishing fourth in the West regional. The 
runner-up in the State Division I championships, he won the team sweepstakes 
race of the prestigious Mt.San Antonio College Invitational in October in 
addition to the Marmonte League and Southern Section Division I championships 
in November. He had a winning record against all the region's top performers, 
including a 2-1 mark against Antonio Arce of Palmdale, a 5-2 record versus 
Brett Strahan of Hart and a 7-1 advantage over Keith O'Doherty of Thousand 
Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 THE REST OF THE TEAM: 
</P>
<P>
 Antonio Arce, Palmdale Sr., placed seventh in the national championships, won 
State and Southern Section Division II titles. Jeff Fischer, Thousand Oaks Sr., 
finished third in the State Division I final as the Lancers won their second 
consecutive title. John Greene, Agoura Sr., the runner-up in the Southern 
Section Division II championships, placed third in the State meet. David Lopez, 
Hoover So., finished eighth in the Southern Section Division I final and 15th 
in the State final. Kevin Marsden, Thousand Oaks Sr., placed fifth in the 
Southern Section Division I championships and ninth in the State meet. Keith 
O'Doherty, Thousand Oaks Sr., the Ventura County champion, finished third in 
the Southern Section Division I final and sixth in the State meet. Javier 
Ramirez, Nordhoff Sr., the Southern Section Division III champion, placed 
second in the State final to propel the Rangers to their second consecutive 
title. Francisco Sandoval, Channel Islands Sr., finished fifth in the Ventura 
County championships. Brett Strahan, Hart Sr., placed fifth in the West 
regional and sixth in the Southern Section Division I championships. 
</P>
