<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL-AREA CROSS-COUNTRY TEAM; TOP GIRLS' RUNNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amy Skieresz 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Agoura 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Skieresz won her third consecutive Ventura County, 
Marmonte League and Southern Section titles and placed first in the State 
Division II championships after winning the Division I title as a junior. In 
addition, she qualified for the Foot Locker national championships for the 
second time in the last three years by finishing fifth in the West 
regional.Although she was disappointed with her 14th-place effort in the 
national meet -- she was third in 1992 -- she was the highest finisher from the 
region. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 THE REST OF THE TEAM: 
</P>
<P>
 Elaine Canchola, Nordhoff Fr., the Southern Section Division III titlist, 
finished second in the West regional and State finals and 19th in the national 
championships. Lorien Cleavinger, Hoover Sr., the Pacific League champion, 
placed 19th in the Southern Section Division I final. Danielle Day, Quartz Hill 
Fr., finished fifth in the Southern Section Division I championships and 18th 
in the State meet. Shaluinn Fullove, Louisville Jr., won the Southern Section 
Division IV title and placed fifth in the State championships. Tara Marsden, 
Thousand Oaks Jr., finished 10th in the Southern Section Division I final and 
13th in the State meet. Kim Mortensen, Thousand Oaks Jr., the runner-up in the 
Southern Section Division I championships, placed fourth in the State meet and 
10th in the West regional. Andrea Neipp, Highland So., the Golden League 
runner-up, finished seventh in the Southern Section Division II championships. 
Bridget Roy, Thousand Oaks Sr., placed fifth in the Ventura County 
championships and ninth in the Southern Section Division I final. Breanne 
Schweitzer, Saugus So., the Foothill League runner-up, finished 22nd in the 
Southern Section Division I championships. 
</P>
