<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; KENNEDY SPARKED BY JANISSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jelani Janisse scored 23 points to lead the Kennedy High basketball team to an 
81-61 victory over Village Christian in the championship game of the Bell-Jeff 
tournament on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Keith Brydon added 12 points and nine rebounds and Trevon Scott scored 14 
points for the Golden Cougars (7-2). Dave Gustafson led Village Christian (5-5) 
with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 73, Chaminade 42 -- Dan Van Etten scored 14 points to lead the 
Pioneers (7-1) in a nonleague game. Scott Blough added 11 and Anthony Tauriello 
and J.J. Washington each had 10 points. Tauriello also had 11 assists. All 10 
Simi Valley players scored. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pioneers put the game away by outscoring Chaminade, 28-10, in the second 
quarter after leading only 10-6 through the first eight minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Arash Safai and Carmine Rossi each scored 12 points to lead the Eagles (5-3). 
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ynez 53, Notre Dame 50 -- Maggie Dixon missed a three-point attempt at 
the buzzer as the Knights lost the third-place game in the Santa Barbara 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior guard Carla Arrue scored a career-high 17 points and had eight rebounds 
for Notre Dame (9-4). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Peninsula 60, Thousand Oaks 44 -- Jenn Detmer had 19 points for Thousand Oaks 
(5-5) in the consolation final of the Santa Barbara tournament. Allison Fortner 
had a game-high 20 points for Peninsula, the defending Southern Section 
Division 1-AA champion. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 55, Ventura 53 -- Angela Mosesso made two free throws with 19.3 
seconds left to break a 53-53 tie and secure third place for the Pioneers 
(11-3) in the Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Mosesso finished with 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Kristen Franklin scored 21 points for Ventura (3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood 62, Chaminade 59 -- All-tournament guard Anna Celaya scored a 
school-record 35 points to lead the Huskies (5-2) in the fifth-place game of 
the Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Celaya, a senior who broke the school's career scoring record Thursday night, 
scored 20 in the first half as North Hollywood took a 29-24 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Sheila Shilati scored 19 points for Chaminade (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 61, Channel Islands 59 -- Tami Ross scored 21 points to lead the 
Golden Cougars (9-5) in the seventh-place game of the Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Channel Islands (5-5) was paced by Danielle Curtis, who scored 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 53, Bell-Jeff 32 -- All-tournament guard LaCresha Clark scored 11 points 
to lead Hart (6-3) to the consolation championship of the Simi Valley 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena 42, Louisville 35 -- Kari Crawley had 10 points and six steals and 
Rosie Chingcuangco added nine points for Louisville (5-6) in the 11th-place 
game of the Simi Valley tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Howard scored 18 points for Pasadena (6-4). 
</P>
